			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hotfix Notes December / 19 / 2007 
<br />
GAMEPLAY
<br />
GENERAL
<br />
- All three spheres have been given a 50% experience bonus during the holidays. The bonus experience will last from Wednesday, December 19th at 5:00am PST to Thursday, January 3rd at 5:00am PST. Enjoy!
<br />
- The weather system has been turned on. Looks like storms are in the forecast!
<br />
- All quests should once again be giving proper rewards.
<br />
- Holiday candy no longer has weight. 
<br />

<br />
ADVENTURING
<br />
- Psionicist – Phrenic Rage should be working correctly now.
<br />
- Shaman – Hayatet Pet damage buff should now be working properly.
<br />
- Warrior – Dual wield now works correctly with crafted weapons.
<br />

<br />
WORLD POPULATION
<br />
- Ancient Port Warehouse - Fixed a water volume issue in APW.
<br />
- Port of Innovus – Ladders should now be functional.
<br />

<br />
ITEMS
<br />
- All instances of bows having double stats should be fixed.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Also, some updates in Build 1933 were not documented in the public release notes. They are as follows:
<br />
- Shaman – Removed all Totems of Release from Shaman trainers. 
<br />
- Celestine Ward – The Celestine Ward armor quests have had their drop rates adjusted and faction rates increased.
<br />
- Celestine Ward – Rarer tomes and runes are now slightly more common.
<br />
- Celestine Ward – Tomes are now slightly more common.
<br />
- Celestine Ward – Candles now drop slightly more frequently.
<br />
- Celestine Ward - Armor pieces now drop at roughly twice their original rate.
<br />
- Celestine Ward - Faction gain for the Celestine Ward has been roughly doubled for all NPC kills.
<br />
- Celestine Ward - Evil races now start with the same amount of faction as good races. 
<br />
- Item - The Core of Ezigoth is now soulbound. 
<br />
- Crafting - Bag recipes have been made a little bit harder</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
