			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's a very different game now, there's been a theme of people who played in beta or at release coming back and trying it out and liking it a lot. It's still not ready for its big re-release imo, but it's getting really close. I think it's a terrific game personally. They've merged the servers into four servers total, so population is pretty good. They've also tweaked it to run much better on a wider range of systems. The /flush command is your friend, god I wish we had that in eq. I don't know anything about the rp really, I don't look for it. The gameplay is very exciting and engrossing to me though, and there's a lot of room for fast, creative thinking on the fly.
<br />

<br />
It's the only mmorpg besides eq1 I've ever liked, and I like it a lot. It needs more marketing, has a bad rep to fight against, and hopefully they do a good re-release when the time comes. In the meantime though, it's been really fun to play. Vanguard gets my vote for sure.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
